subject: Implement Cable schema
commitMessage:
Implement Cable schema

This commit implements Cable and Cable collection schema
on bmcweb.

Testing:
Validator:
@odata.id       /redfish/v1/Cables      odata   Exists  PASS
@odata.type     #CableCollection.CableCollection        odata   Exists
PASS

Yes     PASS

Yes     PASS

Note: Removed some of the fields that are optional to reduce commit msg

Tesing with Curl commands:
$ curl -k -X GET https://{$bmc}/redfish/v1/Cables
{
  "@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Cables",
  "@odata.type": "#CableCollection.CableCollection",
  "Description": "Collection of Cable Entries",
  "Members": [
    {
      "@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Cables/dp0_cable0"
    },

      "@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Cables/dp0_cable1"
    }
  ],
  "Members@odata.count": 2,
  "Name": "Cable Collection"
}

$ curl -k -X GET https://{$bmc}/redfish/v1/Cables/dp0_cable0

  "@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Cables/dp0_cable0",
  "@odata.type": "#Cable.v1_0_0.Cable",
  "CableType": "",
  "Id": "dp0_cable0",
  "Name": "Cable"
}

$ curl -k -X GET https://{$bmc}/redfish/v1/Cables/dp0_cable1
{
  "@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Cables/dp0_cable1",
  "@odata.type": "#Cable.v1_0_0.Cable",
  "CableType": "",
  "Id": "dp0_cable1",
  "Name": "Cable"
}

Set Length property to 1.5 meters using busctl, and check the properties
busctl set-property xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Manager \
 /xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/cables/dp0_cable0 \
 xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item.Cable Length d 1.5

$ curl -k -X GET https://{$bmc}/redfish/v1/Cables/dp0_cable0
{
  "@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Cables/dp0_cable0",
  "@odata.type": "#Cable.v1_0_0.Cable",
  "CableType": "",
  "Id": "dp0_cable0",
  "LengthMeters": 1.5,
  "Name": "Cable"
}

Change has been successfully rebased and submitted as 9c929bea78857633f2b71b356abf4aa4b1ac56d2

I'm not seeing how this result is even possible in the code you wrote.  Are you sure you tested this patchset?  I see nowhere that it's possible to set LengthMeters to null, and even if there were, it would be incorrect.

Yes, that is surprising for me too. I didn't make that up 😊
I tried again just to make sure:
$ curl -k -X GET https://{bmc}:18080/redfish/v1/Cables/dp0_cable0
{
  "@odata.id": "/redfish/v1/Cables/dp0_cable0",
  "@odata.type": "#Cable.v1_0_0.Cable",
  "CableType": "",
  "Id": "dp0_cable0",
  "LengthMeters": null,
  "Name": "dp0_cable0"
}

ok - dbus interface shows "nan" for cable length. 

Skipping "LengthMeters" property for now if the cable length is NaN.

Alternatively, we could set it to 0 or -1 if it is OK.

Keeping this open for discussion.
My vote is to skip if the property is NaN!

> My vote is to skip if the property is NaN!

This isn't a matter of voting.  It's a matter of what phosphor-dbus-interfaces says.  If it doesn't say anything, it needs to, and we can "vote" on the review to add that behavior.

Based on the description for Length in the "Cable.interface.yaml' file, the default value is NaN - that represents a cable of unknown length.

https://grok.openbmc.org/xref/openbmc/phosphor-dbus-interfaces/yaml/xyz/openbmc_project/Inventory/Item/Cable.interface.yaml?r=e52a5257#5

Hope this helps.
Right...... and cables of unknown length should omit the properties in Redfish.  So write your code such that it handles NAN properly.
Ack
Please test the validator on a system that actually has a cable present.  Testing an empty collection only runs ~10% of the code in your patch.
Done
Thanks for the patch!  Looking forward to the fixes.
Please don't reinvent these typedefs.  Please reuse what exists already.  We do this because it significantly deduplicates our templated code.

Here are the two .hpp files that showed-up with typedefs for MapperServiceMap and MapperGetSubTreeResponse/GetSubTreeResponse:
https://grok.openbmc.org/xref/openbmc/pldm/common/utils.hpp?r=872f0f69#151
https://grok.openbmc.org/xref/openbmc/bmcweb/redfish-core/lib/processor.hpp?r=914e2d5d#40

Are you suggesting one of these to include or we have common typedefs somewhere which we can use?

If they are defined somewhere, I would appreciate if you can point it out...

For CableProperties I will see if a common one can be used as well.

Not sure how to proceed on this one as I don't know where the commonly used typedefs are. I prefer to leave it this way for now until I know we can reuse the existing ones. 

I can replace these with actual types wherever these typedefs are used in cable.hpp if that is preferred.

The typedefs in your second link would work just fine.  One thing we're finding is that duplicating the typedefs for the same command duplicates a lot of template code.  Ideally the typedefs in processor should be moved into dbus_utility.
You want me to add MapperServiceMap and MapperGetSubTreeResponse to dbus_util?
Sure, then please move at least one of the existing uses to the new typedef.
Done
Ack
What does the dbus interfaces say about handling when this Length is unavailable.  That needs handled explicitly in your code.

# busctl introspect xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Manager /xyz/openbmc_project/inventory/cables/dp0_cable0
NAME                                     TYPE      SIGNATURE RESULT/VALUE FLAGS
...
xyz.openbmc_project.Inventory.Item.Cable interface -         -            -
.CableTypeDescription                    property  s         ""           emits-change writable
.Length                                  property  d         nan          emits-change writable

not what I asked.  Phosphor-dbus-interfaces will have some statement about what to do when the data isn't available.  we need to handle that.  From the above it sounds like it might be NAN?  If so, we should be using is_finite to ignore the parameter when it's not set.

I used isnan() in patchset2, and it returned true. The default length is NaN as per Cable.interface.yaml file.

Will use isfinite instead of isnan and ignore the parameter. Thanks!
std::is_finite is what we should be using, considering there's more that double can represent that isn't finite.
Ack
Please put this in its own method, and inline the remaining lambda.  WE're already too many scopes deep here, as you can see from the significant line wrapping.
Ack
This is directly called out by name in COMMON_ERRORS.md.  Please read and understand all of those.  in this case, you should be using sdbusplus::message::object_path::filename()

I thought it skips searching path entries early if the map happens to be empty. Will remove as it won't hurt...

?  I suspect name and Id should not be the same here.

That's why we wrote it 😊

This needs bumped to 1_11. How did this pass the Redfish Validator ?

From https://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/ServiceRoot.v1_12_0.json 

              "Cables": {
                    "$ref": "http://redfish.dmtf.org/schemas/v1/CableCollection.json#/definitions/CableCollection",
                    "description": "The link to a collection of cables.",
                    "longDescription": "This property shall contain a link to a resource collection of type CableCollection.",
                    "readonly": true,
                    "versionAdded": "v1_11_0"
                },
Hmmm. I didn't see validator failing for this one but will bump up the version...
Done
